#Text=Choose a Nickname for Your Car
#Text=If you love your car , you might want another way to refer to it other than " my car . "
#Text=However , thinking of car names is n't always easy and it 's understandable if you 're stumped .
#Text=When choosing a nickname for your car , select a name that fits your vehicle 's make and model .
#Text=You should also consider what kind of message you want to convey when you tell other people about your car .
#Text=If you take the time to think about it , you can give your car a name that fits its style and personality .
#Text=Steps
#Text=Brainstorming
#Text=Good Names
#Text=Choose the name of a beautiful person .
#Text=One of the most common ways to name your car is to think of a celebrity or model that you like and give it the same name .
#Text=Try to make the name something that 's uncommon so that people do n't get confused when you refer to your car by its name .
#Text=Some good names include Claire , Stella , Brock , and Venus .
#Text=Name the car after your favorite musician or cartoon character .
#Text=If you 're looking around for names that are n't commonly used for people , you can name the car after a musician or cartoon that you enjoy .
#Text=Think of your favorite band or your favorite character in a cartoon and give your car the same name .
#Text=Car names that are based on musicians or artists include Sid , Beyonce , and Bono .
#Text=Add a prefix or adjective to the name .
#Text=Adding a prefix like Ms. or Mr. will add some character to the car name that you choose .
#Text=If you do n't want to lead the name with that sort of prefix , you can choose an adjective that will help describe the car 's overall look .
#Text=Good adjectives for your name includes colors like white , black , or silver .
#Text=Good starting adjectives for your car include things like super , baby , or old .
#Text=Search online for other popular car names .
#Text=If you ca n't think of an original name , you can get inspired by looking at what other people are naming their cars .
#Text=Search online for car names and look for lists with different car names .
#Text=Scan the lists and find one that suits you and your car .
#Text=Use an online name generator .
#Text=If you 're totally out of ideas and are unsure of what to name your car , you can take an online quiz or name generator to help you determine which name you should choose .
#Text=There are also websites specifically dedicated to generating a name for your car .
#Text=Matching the Name with the Style of the Car
#Text=Base the name on the shape and size of the car .
#Text=Look at the body of your car .
#Text=If it 's blocky , bulky , or powerful , a more masculine name may lend itself better to the car .
#Text=If it 's sleek , sexy , and mysterious , a feminine name may suit it better .
#Text=If the car does n't fit any particular gender stereotypes , you can name it something neutral .
#Text=For example , feminine car names would include Christine , Carolyn , or Shirley .
#Text=Male car names would include The Beast , Charles , and Wolverine .
#Text=Gender neutral names include Tequila Sunrise , Lightning , Alex , or Kelsey .
#Text=Include the make and model in the name .
#Text=Certain car models lend themselves to good car names depending on what they are .
#Text=Determine the kind of car you drive and think of names that can include the model of the car .
#Text=For instance , if you 're driving a Camry , you can name your car Cammie or Cam .
#Text=If you 're driving a Lexus , you can name your car Alexis or Lexie .
#Text=Choose the name based on the type of car you drive .
#Text=Think about whether your car is a pickup truck , sports car , or regular sedan and pick a name that sounds like it applies to the type of car that you have .
#Text=For instance , you would n't want to name a slow truck with the name Supercharged or Red Hot , because it does n't represent the aesthetic of the car .
#Text=Choose a name based on the color .
#Text=There are a variety of more non-conventional names that you can choose based on the color of your car .
#Text=Such names include Silver Surfer , Shadow , Black Magic , Marshmallow , and Ladybug .
#Text=Determine the color of your car and think of names that can relate to the color .
#Text=Other names based on color include Nightcrawler , Cherry Bomb , Mr. Freeze , Cookie Monster , Frogger , Mean Green , and Creamsicle .
#Text=Picking a Name
#Text=Write down all your options .
#Text=Take all of the names that you 're considering for your car and write them down on a piece of paper or type them into a word document .
#Text=Narrow down the names that you do n't like by crossing them out .
#Text=Come back to the list at a later date and continue to narrow down the names until you only have a couple of options left .
#Text=This should help you come up with the perfect name of your car .
#Text=Ask friends and family what they think about the name .
#Text=Once you 've narrowed down your choices or chosen a name , run it by your close family and friends to see what their reaction is .
#Text=Take their suggestions into consideration .
#Text=If there is a name that is wildly popular among many of your friends and family , you can assume that the name is a good one .
#Text=Take your time and stick with the name once you 've chosen it .
#Text=Do n't feel rushed to name your car .
#Text=Instead , take your time and think about the narrowed down choices that you wrote on your list .
#Text=Once you decide on a name , stick with it .
#Text=Constantly changing the name of your car will confuse people and defeats the purpose of naming your car in the first place .
